  "activeTheme": "dadJokes",

  "_doc": [
    "HOW TO USE:",
    "1. Set 'fontFamily' to any Google Font name (e.g. 'Poppins', 'Inter', 'Nunito').",
    "   Register the font in pubspec.yaml under flutter > fonts, or use the google_fonts package.",
    "   Set to null to use the platform default (Roboto on Android, SF Pro on iOS).",
    "",
    "2. Set 'light.seed' and 'dark.seed' to any hex colour (#RRGGBB or #AARRGGBB).",
    "   Material Design 3 generates the full 45-role colour scheme from that one value.",
    "",
    "3. Override individual colour roles under 'light' or 'dark' by replacing null",
    "   with a hex string. Only the roles you fill in are overridden; the rest stay",
    "   seed-generated. This lets you pinpoint-correct a specific colour without",
    "   hand-crafting the entire scheme.",
    "",
    "4. Three ready-made presets are in '_themes' at the bottom of this file.",
    "   All 45 role values were generated by Flutter's ColorScheme.fromSeed().",
    "   To activate one, copy its 'fontFamily', 'light', and 'dark' blocks over",
    "   the top-level fields above '_themes'."
